    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "name": "Ventilation mode",
        "category": "Ventilation",
        "subcategory": "Ventilation mode",
        "shortDescription": "Ventilation mode in use (PCV, VCV, SIMV, pressure support, CPAP/BiPAP, APRV, NAVA, high-frequency, CMV…) — one variable, all modes.",
        "longDescription": "## Definition & Clinical Context\n\nThe ventilation mode is the control strategy a mechanical ventilator uses to deliver breaths — how it triggers, targets and cycles each breath (for example volume-controlled, pressure-controlled, pressure support, CPAP, or high-frequency). In source data this is a single categorical variable per patient-timestamp whose value is the mode in use; it is a **procedure** record with no unit. It is recorded in intensive care and anaesthesia for ventilated patients. The mode is independent of whether ventilation is invasive (via a tube) or non-invasive (via a mask) — that distinction is captured in the Invasive mechanical ventilation and Non-invasive ventilation concept sets.\n\n## Included Concepts\n\nThis set groups all SNOMED ventilation-mode concepts in one place (a single `ventilation_mode` variable). They are organised below by mode family for readability only — all are part of the same set.\n\n### Pressure-controlled (and volume-targeted pressure-control)\n\n- *37152410 / 1186746005 — Assist control ventilation pressure control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *37152412 / 1186748006 — Assist control ventilation pressure-control inflation-type and assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37152411 / 1186747001 — Assist control ventilation volume-targeted pressure-control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *37152408 / 1186744008 — Assist control ventilation volume-targeted pressure-control inflation-type and assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37152364 / 1186622005 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation - pressure-control pressure-support inflation (SNOMED)*\n- *37152384 / 1186679003 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation - volume targeted pressure-control and pressure-support inflation (SNOMED)*\n- *37152386 / 1186681001 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation with pressure-control, two levels of pressure-support and an assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37152387 / 1186682008 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation with pressure-control, one level of pressure-support active during both phases and an assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37152388 / 1186683003 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation with pressure-control, an assured constant airway pressure adjunct and pressure-support at the higher pressure level only (SNOMED)*\n- *37152389 / 1186684009 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation with synchronized termination pressure-control, pressure-support and an assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37152390 / 1186685005 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation with volume targeted pressure-control, pressure-support and an assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n\n### Volume-controlled\n\n- *37152409 / 1186745009 — Assist control ventilation volume-control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *4055375 / 243150007 — Assisted controlled mandatory ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *4245036 / 59427005 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *37152363 / 1186621003 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation - volume control pressure-support inflation (SNOMED)*\n- *37152385 / 1186680000 — Synchronized intermittent mandatory ventilation volume control inflation and an assured constant airway pressure adjunct during expiratory phase (SNOMED)*\n\n### Spontaneous / support\n\n- *37154096 / 1259864003 — Pressure support ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *4165535 / 47545007 — Continuous positive airway pressure ventilation treatment (SNOMED)*\n- *4055262 / 243142003 — Dual pressure spontaneous ventilation support (SNOMED)*\n- *3661883 / 34291000175108 — Nocturnal dual pressure spontaneous ventilation support (SNOMED)*\n- *37152400 / 1186731003 — Continuous spontaneous ventilation with pressure support (SNOMED)*\n- *37152401 / 1186732005 — Continuous spontaneous ventilation with volume targeted pressure-support (SNOMED)*\n- *37152402 / 1186733000 — Continuous spontaneous ventilation with effort support (SNOMED)*\n- *40491848 / 447243000 — Bilevel positive airway pressure titration (SNOMED)*\n- *37152378 / 1186658003 — Spontaneous timed ventilation with pressure-support for spontaneous breaths and volume-control ventilator initiated inflation (SNOMED)*\n- *37152379 / 1186672007 — Spontaneous timed ventilation with pressure-support for spontaneous breaths and pressure-control with flow termination for ventilator initiated inflation (SNOMED)*\n- *37152380 / 1186674008 — Spontaneous timed ventilation with volume targeted pressure-support for spontaneous breaths and volume targeted pressure-control for ventilator initiated inflations (SNOMED)*\n- *37152383 / 1186678006 — Continuous positive airway pressure with an assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37152791 / 1197780003 — Spontaneous and/or timed ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *3661882 / 34281000175105 — Nocturnal continuous positive airway pressure (SNOMED)*\n\n### High-frequency, NAVA, APRV, CMV and other advanced modes\n\n- *4072515 / 243143008 — Airway pressure release ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *37153603 / 1222606000 — Continuous mandatory ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *37153604 / 1222607009 — Continuous mandatory ventilation with sigh (SNOMED)*\n- *37151336 / 1187022003 — Continuous mandatory ventilation volume-control inflation-type and assured constant airway pressure adjunct in the expiratory phase (SNOMED)*\n- *37151337 / 1187023008 — Continuous mandatory ventilation pressure-control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *37151338 / 1187024002 — Continuous mandatory ventilation pressure-control inflation-type and assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37151339 / 1187025001 — Continuous mandatory ventilation volume-targeted pressure-control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *37152413 / 1186749003 — Continuous mandatory ventilation volume-control inflation-type (SNOMED)*\n- *37152407 / 1186742007 — Intermittent mandatory ventilation with synchronized-termination pressure-control and assured constant airway pressure adjunct (SNOMED)*\n- *37157430 / 1217390002 — Intermittent mandatory ventilation with synchronized-termination pressure control and assured constant airway pressure adjunct during the inflation phase (SNOMED)*\n- *37157167 / 1197612007 — Intermittent mandatory ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *37158487 / 1260411001 — Continuous flow apneic ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *4074666 / 243155002 — High frequency oscillatory ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *4055377 / 243154003 — High frequency jet ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *4055376 / 243153009 — High frequency positive pressure ventilation (SNOMED)*\n- *1243692 / 1297240007 — Neurally adjusted ventilatory assist (SNOMED)*\n\n## Mapping Notes\n\n- Map a recorded ventilation mode to the matching concept here, whatever its family. The mode families above are descriptive groupings, not separate sets.\n- **Mode vs ventilation act**: this set is the *mode*; whether the patient is on invasive or non-invasive ventilation is recorded separately (Invasive mechanical ventilation / Non-invasive ventilation concept sets). A patient has both a ventilation act and a mode at the same time.\n- **Dual / volume-targeted pressure-control** modes (e.g. PRVC) are grouped with the pressure-controlled family, since pressure is the controlled variable.\n- **No unit**: the value is the mode itself, not a measurement.\n"
      },
